Modeling global warming

Babich Nikita

2023-06-26

Introduction

Aim: observe evidence of the global warming. Set up: I’ve downloaded a dataset from Kaggle which showed me the following growth on the picture, but I assumed that it could be caused by different starting dates of data collection and continued analysis.

Next step

To make the data consistent I’ve modeled temperature(time) relation for each of biggest countries. Red line - parabolic model.

Other several countries

Only two exceptions

All countries I looked into had a definite growth and acceleration of temperature. But these 2 countries had the temperature slowing down! But that is non-significant in the scale of the Earth.

Conclusion

Using land area as weight I found the weighted averages of polynomial models’ coefficients and got the results: 7.557291 for linear coefficient, 0.985371 for parabolic coefficient. That means temperature grows AND grows faster with each year.
